      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You want to know about the old tropes, huh? Alright, let me tell you, there are some classics. Here are 5 common racial stereotypes that Hollywood has been using for decades:\n\n1. The \"angry black woman\" - you know, the one who's always yelling and being dramatic. You can flip this on its head by making her the voice of reason or a comedic relief.\n\n2. The \"nerdy Asian guy\" - the one who's always good at math and science, but socially awkward. You can subvert this by making him a charismatic leader or a cool, laid-back character.\n\n3. The \"Latin lover\" - the charming, passionate, and seductive guy from Latin America. You can flip this by making him a complex, multi-dimensional character with flaws and weaknesses.\n\n4. The \"white savior complex\" - where a white character is the hero who saves people of color from themselves. You can subvert this by making the hero a person of color or by showing the complexity of the situation.\n\n5. The \"exotic Asian woman\" - the one who's always dressed in traditional clothing and is mysterious and alluring. You can flip this by making her a strong, independent character with",
